The term '''Akashaganga''' is a [[Sanskrit language|Sanskrit]] word (etymology: Akasha + Ganga = Sky River (or) [[river]] in the [[sky]]) and can refer to any of the following: -

* Widely used name in the [[India]]n vernacular languages to refer to our [[galaxy]], the [[Milky way]].
* A concept about the river [[Ganga]] which states that the river has three components, the Akasha Ganga - which flows in the [[heaven]]s, the Ganga - which then descends on to [[earth]] and Patalganga - which empties itself into the [[Naraka|underworld]].
* Name of the waterfalls located in [[Tirumala - Tirupati]], [[Andhra Pradesh]], [[India]], a place of pilgrimage and piety for [[Hindu]]s.

